transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Yeah, I just received an order that I did not order.

Speaker 2: We can take a look for you.

Speaker 1: Trying to pull up an account for you.

Speaker 2: What's your, is it speaking to Larry?

Speaker 1: Yeah, my name's Larry.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, it seems like that's one of your refills.

Speaker 1: You do not have to do it that way though.

Speaker 2: I did not check for automatic refills.

Speaker 1: I absolutely did not check for automatic refills.

Speaker 2: My initial order was a one-time order.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, I understand.

Speaker 2: So basically the only way to go out like that is if you do not set it up to be a one-time order?

Speaker 1: Or if you don't let us know when you want your order to come out?

Speaker 2: That's the only way it'll come out, the way the doctor writes a prescription.

Speaker 1: So I do understand, I mean, I believe since you didn't hit anything,

Speaker 2: that is why that came out here like that.

Speaker 1: But we can fix that for you now.

Speaker 2: Well, I, yeah, I don't want these.

Speaker 1: I didn't order them.

Speaker 2: Well, you got the same thing you ordered the first time, sir.

Speaker 1: I know.

Speaker 2: And my order was a one-time order.

Speaker 1: I did not order automatic refills.

Speaker 2: Yeah, correct, sir.

Speaker 1: So the automatic refills started because you neglected to choose how you wanted your order to come out or to choose a one-time.

Speaker 2: I can call my credit card company and cancel this transaction.

Speaker 1: You can also just listen to me explain this because you can go to a credit card company

Speaker 2: and I can tell you what they're going to tell you.

Speaker 1: They're going to tell you that you need to call us and then they're going to contact us

Speaker 2: and I'm going to give them this recorded call of me trying to help you.

Speaker 1: And we can refund you, just, you know, giving you customer service.

Speaker 2: So, I mean, whatever you'd like to do, sir.

Speaker 1: You want to waste your own time?

Speaker 2: It didn't sound like you were getting ready to be offering a refund.

Speaker 1: No, sir.

Speaker 2: I'm just kind of instructing you on what's going on and how it happened and stuff like that.

Speaker 1: Don't worry, sir.

Speaker 2: This is just too much trouble.

Speaker 1: We're going to cancel you out.

Speaker 2: You'll never order from us again, okay?

Speaker 1: You have a great day.

Speaker 2: That's right.
